rComments: I took intermediate Turkish with Lale and she's a great teacher!  She explains the grammar very clearly.  She's also seems genuinely  passionate about Turkish language, culture, and literature, which made the class all the more interesting.

Lale is an amazing prof. She tries very hard for you to succeed in your class, is always available for extra help and always interacts with students. She teaches you the language and teaches you the culture. She is an amazing teacher and an amazing person. Definitely take her courses if you can

It was the BEST course I've taken ever. Lale is an expert on the Turkish language and has everything you want to find in a professor. She is approachable, engaging and respectful. I had 0 knowledge of Turkish and I was worried at start but by the end of the semester I was able to read and speak Turkish! I highly recommend courses with her.

She's a graduate student who's given a task beyond her capacity. In order to teach a language course (intro level, in particular) one has to be super accurate (i.e. grammar, spelling, etc) which she isn't. That's only one issue to keep in mind when dealing with this teacher. DO NOT take this class with her unless you are a native Turkish speaker.

Lale is genuinely invested her students' learning. She created an environment where I felt comfortable asking questions and seeking extra help. She was very helpful when I did need additional help and I felt inspired to do well in the class because of her encouragement. She embodies all the positive traits a student looks for in an instructor.
Very good class that I looked forward to!
